@18005 = ~Shadow Thief Report~
@18006 = ~A handwritten transcript, detailing a meeting between one Lady Katarina, and Lord Dominick. Some member of the Shadow Thieves has crafted this extensive document, meticulously capturing even  Lord Dominick's more banal ramblings. A few passages catch your eye:

Lady Katarina: I salute your taste,  my Lord Dominic,  exactly the delightful earthy tones you described- my, is that the bottle gone? One might suspect a less honorable and handsome man of plying me with drink... oh, but wait, we still need another bottle! I meant to toast the Hero of Baldur's Gate, and hear the story of how you knew them!
Dominick: I… I apoloshize, my lady, when I said I knew the Hero, I meant more from... um, afar. I was there, though, Baldur's Gate, when they saved the city! Me and my father, we were vishiting... right, right in the thick of it on a visit, heard of the near war, everything!
Lady Katarina: Oh. What a sly rascal, to have deceived so... You wouldn't lie to me now that we are such good friends, would you, my dear?
Dominick: Never, Mish Katarina. You can trust me. They were so brave and incredible. The evil war… warrior Sarevok was killing everyone and it was he who nearly started the war! The hero came from Candlekeep and they were related! Related, I say!
Lady Katarina: Do continue! I cannot deny an appetite for such gossip... have you heard anything of the Hero being here Amn? Have you any notion of why they might be?
Dominick: OH, yesh! First there wasesh this mad mage Irenikish and he caught the hero becaush he was a CH… ILD OF BHAAAL and...

The remainder of the transcript becomes increasingly incoherent, as Lord Dominic's inebriation overcomes first intelligibility and then, eventually, consciousness.~

